    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Professional fabricators participate in producing a finished product; they are responsible for a step or process, for the creation of parts, or for assembling parts into a finished product. In the creation of artworks, fabricators are artisans or other people involved with producing large or technically difficult artworks, where resources are required beyond an individual artist's to produce the work.</Note_Text>
